      "id": "{folderName}-001",
      "url": "{exact file path url as provided in the script output}",
      "alt": "...",
      "category": "...",
      "isPremium": false
    }
  ]
}
```

Rules:
- Generate an entry for **every image** in the script output. Do not skip any.
- `id`: folderName + zero-padded index e.g. `lgbtq-001`, `lgbtq-002`
- `url`: use the **exact file path/url as provided in the script output** — do not construct or modify it
- `alt`: 15–25 words. Unique per image. Written for **inspirational search intent** — the user is browsing for design ideas, so alts should feel evocative and visual, like a mood board caption. Naturally include the high-traffic keyword patterns you found in your SERP research. Mention nail style, colors, finish, and vibe/occasion. Use the existing blog alt only as context to understand the image — never copy it.
- `category`: infer dominant color or style from the filename e.g. `"rainbow"`, `"purple"`, `"french"`, `"chrome"`, `"glitter"`, `"nude"`
- `isPremium`: set `true` for roughly 1 in every 8 images, spread out — not clustered at the start
- No `dimensions` field

